{"_id":"B3gVnp8czFI7DZk3","name":"_READ THIS","content":"<h1>Instructions</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>First Time</h2>\n<p>You only need to import the macros from the <strong>Auto Update Macros</strong> compendium.</p>\n<p>You can do that openning the compendium and importing the folders inside it.</p>\n<p>Now, after each update for the Macros for SWADE module your macros will be updated.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>New Macros</h2>\n<p>If a new macro were uploaded you can check it out in the compendium <strong>Auto Update Macros</strong>. You can right click the macro and click <strong>Import Entry</strong>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Old Users</h2>\n<p>If you imported the macros from the compendium Macros for SWADE you'll have to delete the old macro and import the newer version for each update. This is not recommended because it's very boring.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Incompatibility</h2>\n<p>This module may not work well with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/League-of-Foundry-Developers/fvtt-advanced-macros\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Advanced Macros</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/lipefl/swade-tools\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SWADE Tools</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n<p>You need to install:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Larkinabout/fvtt-challenge-tracker\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Challenge Tracker</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/earlSt1/vtt-compendium-folders\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Compendium Folders</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trioderegion/warpgate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Warp Gate</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Documentation</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.dyHC5k4Tlah2dAek]{Common Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.Gxe7Suuu2hfKM7j0]{Macros for Players}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.WkRZaEEGuCSSqp5R]{Macros for Settings}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.0xdxcUQkKDS0XbF2]{GM Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.lWtA4s31kzgkF1qt]{Special Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.26R0M4mnq6TPjaRs]{Alchemy}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.geegW768mdCsQ8ur]{API - Create your own Macros}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.PpSCLfufdR6THMeA]{Create an Additional Stat}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h1>Tips</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Recommended Modules</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Better Roll 2: SWADE Automation</li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Custom CSS: </span>This module let you change undesired visual things easily.</li>\n<li>Permission Viewer: You need to know what macros will be shared with the players. This module helps with that.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Gxe7Suuu2hfKM7j0","name":"Macros for Players","content":"<h1>Macros for Players</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/movement/chevrons-down-yellow.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Boost/Lower Trait</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Target one or more tokens. </li>\n<li>Select if you want to boost or lower a trait. </li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/time/arrows-circling-pink.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Equip/Unequip Set</h2>\n<p>You can create two sets of items that can be swapped. Example: You have a crossbow (set 1) and a sword and shield. You can execute the macro to change between them. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open your actor sheet.</li>\n<li>You need to add to <strong>Description</strong> of the items <strong>#equipSet1</strong> or <strong>#equipSet2</strong>. Capitalization matter.</li>\n<li>When you run the macro it will equip set one and disable set two and if you execute again it will reverse this.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/magic/death/undead-ghost-scream-teal.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Fear</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>You must select the fear source and the fear modifier.</li>\n<li>It'll test your spirit and check the result.</li>\n<li>Then it'll run Fear Table set in <strong>Macros for SWADE settings</strong>. </li>\n<li>It'll try to apply some status.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/fear-macro.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"176\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/life/cross-area-circle-green-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Healing</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>Natural Healing and Skill Healing</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can select and target a token. If you do this, the roll for Skill Healing will not heal the selected token. It'll tell about a attempt to heal the target.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/books/book-embossed-spiral-purple-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Spellbook Manager</h2>\n<p>You can create three sets of powers that can be swapped. Example: You have a Bolt, Confusion (set 1), Healing and Confusion (set 2). You can execute the macro to change between them. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open your actor sheet.</li>\n<li>You need to add to <strong>Description</strong> of the powers <strong>#</strong><strong>spellBook1</strong>,<strong> </strong><strong>#</strong><strong>spellBook2 </strong>or <strong>#spellBook3</strong>. Capitalization matter.</li>\n<li>When you run the macro it will equip set one and disable set two and if you execute again it will reverse this.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/magic/symbols/elements-air-earth-fire-water.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Power Point Management</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/magic/earth/construct-stone.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Summon Actor</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a folder in the Actors directory and add the actors you want to summon in a scene.</li>\n<li>Import the macro <strong>Summon Actor</strong> from the <strong>Macros for SWADE</strong> compendium. Look at the first line of it. You need to set the folder name equal to yours. Look at the example.</li>\n<li>Run the macro and select or search for the actor in the box.</li>\n<li>Click on a scene to summon it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Example</strong></p>\n<p>const folderName = 'Bestiary';  // Replace Bestiary for your folder name.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Important!</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The player need the Token Permission on Foundry VTT settings.</li>\n<li>The player need permission to the actors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Use Cases</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>This is useful for summons.</li>\n<li>This is a simple way to shape shifting. The player just add the new shape.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You need to install:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trioderegion/warpgate/releases/latest/download/module.json\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Warp Gate</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Support</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target another one.</li>\n<li>You can now select a skill to support and check out the target skill list.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/skills/ranged/arrow-strike-apple-orange.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Test</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target another one. Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If you check the Creative Combat box, it'll run the table for you.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Unshaken</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If the token is shaken it will offer to roll spirit and spend a benny on failure.</li>\n<li>If the token is unshaken it will set the Shaken status to it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/symbols/symbol-lightning-bolt.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Unstun</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>If the token is stunned it will offer to roll vigor and spend a benny on failure.</li>\n<li>If the token is unstunned it will set the stunned status to it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/tools/nautical/steering-wheel.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Vehicle Maneuvers</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>It's a macro for quick query rules.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8A8MXeQUcdCXOOtn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swademacros.guide-macros-for-swade.AhCtirFF3m2Qy1Oz"}}}
{"_id":"PpSCLfufdR6THMeA","name":"Create an Additional Stat","content":"<h1>Additional Stats</h1>\n<p>You can create extra fields the actor sheet or in the items.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <strong>Configure Settings</strong>.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>System Settings</strong> </li>\n<li>Click <strong>Open Setting Configurator</strong>.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Additional Stats</strong>.</li>\n<li>Add one to actors or items. You can pick some kinds of fields. Number, Text, etc.</li>\n<li>Save it.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aditionalstats1.webp\" width=\"601\" height=\"572\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Now you need to activate it for each actor sheet or item. </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click in <strong>Tweaks</strong> in the actor sheet or item sheet.</li>\n<li>Check enable for the <strong>Additional Stat</strong> you want.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aditionalstats2.webp\" width=\"384\" height=\"726\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8A8MXeQUcdCXOOtn":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"teste-savageworlds","system":"swade","coreVersion":"0.8.9","systemVersion":"0.21.3"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.EzbU7KCX3HsxGZDr"}}}
{"_id":"WkRZaEEGuCSSqp5R","name":"Macros for Settings","content":"<p> </p>\n<h1>Deadlands</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"modules/deadlands-core-rules/assets/icons/deadlands-logo.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Adventure Generator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>It'll show the possible adventure in the chat. If you liked it, you can click the button to create a Journal with it. Do not require to import the tables.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h1>Sprawlrunners</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/treasure/puzzle-box-glowing-blue.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> LP Check</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>All players with a character selected will have their Logistics Points accounted from the itens.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Important</strong></p>\n<p>The item must be equipped or it'll not count.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>You must set Additional Stats in System Settings like the image:</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/sprawllpcheck.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"547\" /></p>\n<p>Then, you must enable it in the Actor Sheet.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/sprawllpcheck2.webp\" width=\"625\" height=\"697\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/351063/Sprawlrunners--FoundryVTT-Module\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sprawlrunners - FoundryVTT-Module</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/tech/antenna-powered-purple.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Cyberspace Actions</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>The player must choose 1 action only. It'll send to the chat the action.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/cyberspaceactions.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"279\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/351063/Sprawlrunners--FoundryVTT-Module\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sprawlrunners - FoundryVTT-Module</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/commodities/currency/coins-plain-gold.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Coin Manager for Savage Pathfinder</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one or more tokens and run the macro.</li>\n<li>You can add or remove coins from the selected token.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This macro will create the items on the tokens.</li>\n<li>The tokens must be a linked token.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://peginc.com/store/pathfinder-for-savage-worlds-foundryvtt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Pathfinder for Savage Worlds – FoundryVTT</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dyHC5k4Tlah2dAek","name":"Common Macros","content":"<h1>Macros for SWADE</h1>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/tools/navigation/sextant-steel-blue.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> 3D Measure</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token and target other tokens. </li>\n<li>It'll display to the chat the distance between then calculating <strong>height</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/3dMeasure.webp\" width=\"344\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-green.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Active Effect Builder</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select or target some tokens. You can mix target and select.</li>\n<li>Type a desired name.</li>\n<li>Choose the AE type and define a value.</li>\n<li>All tokens will receive that active effect.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Note 1: It will get the skill list only from the first selected token.</p>\n<p>Note 2: If you don't change the name it'll try to auto name the AE.</p>\n<p>Note 3: If you don't add turns it will ignore timed effects.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/aebuilder.webp\" width=\"452\" height=\"387\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Notes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It'll guess the best mode.</li>\n<li>true/false effects will always start true.</li>\n<li>Players can use this macro. Very useful for powers like this: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.DPOBFvSuvQgDWF2c]{Protection}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Macro Managers</h2>\n<p>You can use the managers to open a menu with the main macros for each role. It'll only work after you import all macros.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can change the macros that will appear in the manager by switching the names by the ones you desire. You need to get the actual macro, and not the Auto Update one.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>  const macros = [</p>\n<p>    \"Macro 1\",</p>\n<p>    \"Macro 2\"</p>\n<p>  ];</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>GM - Macro Manager</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/gmmacromanager.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"169\" /></p>\n<p>Player - Macro Manager</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/playermacromanager.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"132\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/creatures/mammals/wolf-shadow-black.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Gang Up</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one token.</li>\n<li>Target another token.</li>\n<li>Run the macro. It'll calculate the Ganging Up bonus. </li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Important</p>\n<p>This macro uses token disposition to indentify friend from foe. Be sure to set them property.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Module</p>\n<p>Token Faction is recommended.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/magic/time/arrows-circling-pink.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Next Turn</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>It'll skip the current turn if are in combat.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/skills/movement/arrow-upward-yellow.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Raise Calculator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n<li>It'll update the success level as you type.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/raisecalc.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"163\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/tools/hand/scale-balances-merchant-brown.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Size/Scale Calculator</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Target another one.</li>\n<li>Run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/lights/torch-brown-lit.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Token Vision</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Select one or more tokens and run the macro.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"geegW768mdCsQ8ur","name":"API - Create your own Macros","content":"<h1>API - Create your own Macros</h1>\n<p>You can call some shortcuts from Macros for SWADE to make easier to write your own macros. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Basics</h2>\n<p>tokenD is defined as:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>let tokenD=canvas.tokens.controlled[0];</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can make a quick test.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the console (F12).</li>\n<li>Select a token.</li>\n<li>Paste: let tokenD=canvas.tokens.controlled[0];</li>\n<li>Paste: sm.getMaxWounds(tokenD)</li>\n<li>This will return the token max wounds.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\">Load API</h2>\n<p>Before use any function with sm.??? you need to load the API.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>const sm = game.modules.get('swademacros')?.api.sm;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<p>This will read a selected token and will return a item <strong>itemName</strong> if it is present.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getItem(tokenD, itemName);</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This will read a selected token and will try to remove a item <strong>itemName</strong> if it is present. You need to check for it before.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getItem(tokenD, itemName);</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Add/remove wounds</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.applyWounds(tokenD, val)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Add/remove wounds for a target token which a player don't own</p>\n<blockquote style=\"border-left:3px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary)\">\n<p>sm.applyWoundsForNotOwnedToken(tokenD, val)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Return max wounds.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getMaxWounds(tokenD)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Return current wounds.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getWounds(tokenD)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Add/remove fatique</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.applyFatigue(tokenD, val)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Return max fatigue.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getFatigue(tokenD)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Return current fatigue.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getMaxFatigue(tokenD)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Styled text message. You don't need to use iconPath, but you can set a path to a image.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.styledChatMessage('Title Text', 'Text', 'IconPath');</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Add a active effect to a token.</p>\n<blockquote style=\"border-left:3px solid var(--color-border-light-tertiary)\">\n<p>sm.addActiveEffect(tokenD, activeEffectData, type)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The <span style=\"font-style:italic;font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">activeEffectData should follow one of the models below. The warpgate model let a player change a not owned token. The Foundry VTT model just let the player change the tokens he owns. The GM can change anything. To use the warp gate model set type to true. To use the Foundry VTT model set type to false.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Foundry VTT Model Example</span></strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>const myActiveEffect = {</em></p>\n<p><em>  changes: [</em></p>\n<p><em>    {\"key\":\"data.stats.speed.value\", \"mode\":CONST.ACTIVE_EFFECT_MODES.OVERRIDE, \"value\":\"12\"}</em></p>\n<p><em>  ],</em></p>\n<p><em>  icon: 'icons/consumables/potions/potion-jar-corked-green.webp',</em></p>\n<p><em>  label: itemName</em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>}  </em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Warpgate Model Example</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>    const activeEffectData = {</p>\n<p>      embedded: {</p>\n<p>        ActiveEffect:{ </p>\n<p>          label: {</p>\n<p>            label: `${raise ? \"major\" : \"minor\"} ${direction} ${trait.name}`,</p>\n<p>            icon: direction == \"Lower\" ? DOWNICON : UPICON,</p>\n<p>            changes: [{                    </p>\n<p>              \"key\": trait[\"diekey\"],</p>\n<p>              \"mode\": 2,</p>\n<p>              \"value\": diemod,</p>\n<p>              \"priority\": 0</p>\n<p>            },{</p>\n<p>              \"key\": trait[\"modkey\"],</p>\n<p>              \"mode\": 2,</p>\n<p>              \"value\": modmod,</p>\n<p>              \"priority\": 0</p>\n<p>            }],</p>\n<p>            duration: {</p>\n<p>              \"rounds\": direction == \"Lower\" ? 1 : 5</p>\n<p>            },</p>\n<p>            flags: {</p>\n<p>              swade: {</p>\n<p>                \"expiration\": 3,</p>\n<p>              }</p>\n<p>            }</p>\n<p>          }</p>\n<p>        }</p>\n<p>      }      </p>\n<p>    };  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Remove an active effect with this label: activeEffectLabel.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.removeActiveEffect(tokenD, activeEffectLabel)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Return the active effect with this label: activeEffectLabel</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>sm.getActiveEffect(tokenD, activeEffectLabel)   </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dJvi2seC8CqTkxhs":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.VJxzWsJevOvzGEm8"}}}
{"_id":"lWtA4s31kzgkF1qt","name":"Special Macros","content":"<h2>Special Macros</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/tools/navigation/map-chart-tan.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Feet To SWADE</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>DO NOT USE THIS MACRO UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DOING</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This macro will read the active scene and change the size of wall lights. <strong>THIS CAN'T BE UNDONE</strong>. </p>\n<p>If you install any map from foundry it'll came with 5 ft square and the lights set to this. This macro will fix the lights for you. You should duplicate a scene before run this.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/feettoswade01.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"423\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/feettoswade02.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"360\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><img src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/rune-card.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Images To Folder</h2>\n<p>This macro will read all images in a folder and create a journal with each image inside a folder in the journal tab.</p>\n<p>It's useful for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>create your own action deck</li>\n<li>create an adventure deck</li>\n<li>add lots of image handouts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For action deck you can just export the folder to a compendium and click <strong>Open in Action Card Editor</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/imagestofolder01.webp\" width=\"600\" height=\"490\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1. Run the macro.</p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/swademacros/docs/imagestofolder02.webp\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2 style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\"><img style=\"border:1px solid var(--color-border-dark)\" src=\"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards-brown.webp\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /> Image Folder to Deck</h2>\n<p>This macro will read all images in a folder and create a deck with each image being card.</p>\n<p>It's useful for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>create your own action deck</li>\n<li>create an adventure deck</li>\n</ul>","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"tckKxzbezKvre3KI":3},"flags":{}}
